						               													<description>Mar&amp;atilde;n&amp;aacute; is a simple and strategic card game for 2 to 3 people with a focus on battle and inspired by brazilian native american culture. It uses unique positioning mechanics in three rows and four columns for each player. The position of each warrior card is crucial in determining who he can attack. The base game comes with 3 decks of 30 cards each and all cards are unique. In the match setup, you choose 20 of the 30 cards for that match. Each warrior is unique and has Strength and Dodge values that allow these characters to attack, counterattack or dodge in combat, creating an immersive and intense game. Strength or Dodge points earn a bonus from a D4 to increase the variability of combats and make them more real. No warrior is able to return once they have been defeated and the objective of the game is to leave the opponent's field without any card on it, which means instant victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
